Hi Wladimyr,

Look like the problem is coming from some environment variable (or path) that 
are set correctly in your user account and incorrectly in the root account. I 
would follow-up on Michele&#39;s idea with checking the following commands from 
both root and your user account:

which python
echo $PYTHON_CMD
echo $PYTHONPATH
which ctpython

I would personnaly flavor the do &quot;configure&quot; and &quot;make&quot; as a regular user and 
do only &quot;make install&quot; as root (or even better do everything from an admin 
account and install in a shared location. This way you can mess with the 
environment variables without touching your root account).

I hope this help.

Julien



